      </p>
      <div class="assembly-hero-note reveal">
        <span class="assembly-hero-note-label">Current Status</span>
        <p>The Founding Assembly is being constituted. We are in dialogue with organizations across healthcare, finance, government, and technology.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- ============================================
     THE MODEL: WHY THIS IS DIFFERENT
     ============================================ -->
<section class="assembly-model">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="assembly-model-header">
      <span class="label label--accent reveal">The Model</span>
      <h2 class="assembly-model-title reveal">This Is Not Traditional Partnership</h2>
      <p class="assembly-model-sub reveal">
        The Founding Assembly reflects a fundamentally different relationship between institutions and civic infrastructure.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="assembly-model-comparison reveal">
      <div class="assembly-model-col assembly-model-col--old">
        <h3 class="assembly-model-col-title">Traditional Sponsorship</h3>
        <ul class="assembly-model-list">
          <li>You pay for visibility</li>
          <li>Logo placement</li>
          <li>Reserved seats</li>
          <li>Benefits you receive</li>
          <li>Open to all with budget</li>
          <li>Transaction</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="assembly-model-col assembly-model-col--new">
        <h3 class="assembly-model-col-title">The Founding Assembly</h3>
        <ul class="assembly-model-list">
          <li>You're vetted for alignment</li>
          <li>Name in historical record</li>
          <li>Required participation</li>
          <li>Obligations you accept</li>
          <li>Invitation only, capped at 25</li>
          <li>Commitment</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="assembly-model-principle reveal">
      <blockquote class="assembly-model-quote">
        "The 25 Founding Institutions will be permanently recorded as the organizations that chose to build—not buy—civic infrastructure for AI."
      </blockquote>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- ============================================
     SELECTION CRITERIA
     ============================================ -->
<section class="assembly-criteria">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="assembly-criteria-header">
      <span class="label label--accent reveal">Selection Criteria</span>
      <h2 class="assembly-criteria-title reveal">What We Look For</h2>
      <p class="assembly-criteria-sub reveal">
        Founding Institutions are not solicited. They are identified based on public evidence of alignment with our mission. We evaluate:
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="assembly-criteria-grid">
      <div class="assembly-criteria-card reveal">
        <span class="assembly-criteria-num">01</span>
        <div>
          <h3 class="assembly-criteria-name">Demonstrated AI Commitment</h3>
          <p class="assembly-criteria-desc">A public track record of responsible AI work—not press releases, but evidence. Published research, implemented governance frameworks, or substantive contributions to AI policy discourse.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="assembly-criteria-card reveal reveal-d1">
        <span class="assembly-criteria-num">02</span>
        <div>
          <h3 class="assembly-criteria-name">Cross-Sector Relevance</h3>
          <p class="assembly-criteria-desc">Your organization must operate within or directly impact at least one of our four focus sectors: healthcare, finance, government, or technology. We seek institutions whose AI decisions ripple across society.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="assembly-criteria-card reveal reveal-d2">
        <span class="assembly-criteria-num">03</span>
        <div>
          <h3 class="assembly-criteria-name">Leadership Engagement</h3>
          <p class="assembly-criteria-desc">The CEO or equivalent must be personally engaged. This is not delegable to CSR or marketing. Founding Institutions are led by individuals who understand that AI governance is existential, not promotional.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="assembly-criteria-card reveal reveal-d3">
        <span class="assembly-criteria-num">04</span>
        <div>
          <h3 class="assembly-criteria-name">Contribution Capacity</h3>
          <p class="assembly-criteria-desc">Ability to meaningfully contribute beyond financial commitment. Can you host sessions? Provide domain expertise? Extend distribution of Civic Briefs to policymakers? We seek active builders, not passive supporters.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="assembly-criteria-card reveal reveal-d4">
        <span class="assembly-criteria-num">05</span>
        <div>
          <h3 class="assembly-criteria-name">Values Alignment</h3>
          <p class="assembly-criteria-desc">Commitment to stakeholder capitalism, not shareholder primacy. We seek institutions that measure success by societal impact, not just financial returns. Your organization's actions must reflect this—we review the record.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="assembly-criteria-card reveal reveal-d5">
        <span class="assembly-criteria-num">06</span>
        <div>
          <h3 class="assembly-criteria-name">Long-Term Orientation</h3>
          <p class="assembly-criteria-desc">This is a permanent commitment to civic infrastructure. We seek institutions building for decades, not quarters. The Founding Assembly is not a marketing opportunity—it's a historical responsibility.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- ============================================
     WHAT'S REQUIRED
     ============================================ -->
<section class="assembly-requirements">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="assembly-requirements-header">
      <span class="label label--accent reveal">Requirements</span>
      <h2 class="assembly-requirements-title reveal">What's Expected of Founding Institutions</h2>
      <p class="assembly-requirements-sub reveal">
        Joining the Founding Assembly is not transactional. It comes with obligations. Here is what we require:
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="assembly-requirements-grid">
      <div class="assembly-requirement reveal">
        <div class="assembly-requirement-icon">
          <svg width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5">
            <path d="M17 21v-2a4 4 0 0 0-4-4H5a4 4 0 0 0-4 4v2"/>
            <circle cx="9" cy="7" r="4"/>
            <path d="M23 21v-2a4 4 0 0 0-3-3.87"/>
            <path d="M16 3.13a4 4 0 0 1 0 7.75"/>
          </svg>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h3 class="assembly-requirement-title">Active Participation</h3>
          <p class="assembly-requirement-desc">Send at least two diverse representatives to each TownSquare session. Not just executives—we require voices from different levels of your organization. Presence is mandatory, not optional.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="assembly-requirement reveal reveal-d1">
        <div class="assembly-requirement-icon">
          <svg width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5">
            <path d="M14 2H6a2 2 0 0 0-2 2v16a2 2 0 0 0 2 2h12a2 2 0 0 0 2-2V8z"/>
            <polyline points="14,2 14,8 20,8"/>
            <line x1="16" y1="13" x2="8" y2="13"/>
            <line x1="16" y1="17" x2="8" y2="17"/>
          </svg>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h3 class="assembly-requirement-title">The Readiness Pledge</h3>
          <p class="assembly-requirement-desc">Make a public commitment to your own organization's AI readiness. This means transparent reporting on your internal AI governance, workforce preparation, and ethical frameworks. We hold each other accountable.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="assembly-requirement reveal reveal-d2">
        <div class="assembly-requirement-icon">
          <svg width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5">
            <circle cx="12" cy="12" r="10"/>
            <path d="M12 6v6l4 2"/>
          </svg>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h3 class="assembly-requirement-title">Contribution</h3>
          <p class="assembly-requirement-desc">Each Founding Institution contributes beyond attendance. Host a TownSquare session in your city. Provide facilitators from your domain. Extend distribution of Civic Briefs to your network. Build the infrastructure.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="assembly-requirement reveal reveal-d3">
        <div class="assembly-requirement-icon">
          <svg width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5">
            <path d="M22 11.08V12a10 10 0 1 1-5.93-9.14"/>
            <polyline points="22 4 12 14.01 9 11.01"/>
          </svg>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h3 class="assembly-requirement-title">Annual Accountability</h3>
          <p class="assembly-requirement-desc">Submit to annual review of your organization's AI readiness progress. Founding Institutions lead by example—your journey toward AI readiness becomes part of the collective record, with transparency to the Assembly.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- ============================================
     THE CHARTER (PREVIEW)
     ============================================ -->
<section class="assembly-charter">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="assembly-charter-inner reveal">
      <div class="assembly-charter-badge">The Founding Charter</div>
      <h2 class="assembly-charter-title">What You Sign</h2>
      <p class="assembly-charter-intro">
        Upon acceptance into the Founding Assembly, your organization's leadership signs the Founding Institution Charter. This is a public commitment, not a private contract. The Charter includes:
      </p>
      <div class="assembly-charter-items">
        <div class="assembly-charter-item">
          <span class="assembly-charter-check">&#10003;</span>
          <span>Commitment to active participation in TownSquare sessions</span>
        </div>
        <div class="assembly-charter-item">
          <span class="assembly-charter-check">&#10003;</span>
          <span>The Readiness Pledge for your own organization</span>
        </div>
        <div class="assembly-charter-item">
          <span class="assembly-charter-check">&#10003;</span>
          <span>Agreement to annual accountability reporting</span>
        </div>
        <div class="assembly-charter-item">
          <span class="assembly-charter-check">&#10003;</span>
          <span>Pledge to extend, not gatekeep, AI readiness knowledge</span>
        </div>
        <div class="assembly-charter-item">
          <span class="assembly-charter-check">&#10003;</span>
          <span>Recognition that this is a permanent, historical commitment</span>
        </div>
      </div>
      <p class="assembly-charter-note">
        The Charter is signed by the CEO or equivalent. It is published alongside the names of all Founding Institutions as a public record.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- ============================================
     WHAT JOINING MEANS
     ============================================ -->
<section class="assembly-outcomes">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="assembly-outcomes-header">
      <span class="label label--accent reveal">Natural Outcomes</span>
      <h2 class="assembly-outcomes-title reveal">What Membership Means</h2>
      <p class="assembly-outcomes-sub reveal">
        We don't offer "benefits"—we describe what naturally follows from being part of the Founding Assembly:
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="assembly-outcomes-grid">
      <div class="assembly-outcome reveal">
        <h3 class="assembly-outcome-title">Historical Record</h3>
        <p class="assembly-outcome-desc">Your institution's name appears in every Civic Brief as a Founding Institution. Not a logo—a name, in the permanent record of this movement.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="assembly-outcome reveal reveal-d1">
        <h3 class="assembly-outcome-title">Direct Dialogue</h3>
        <p class="assembly-outcome-desc">Your representatives engage directly with cross-sector leaders shaping AI policy. These conversations happen in structured civic dialogue, not networking events.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="assembly-outcome reveal reveal-d2">
        <h3 class="assembly-outcome-title">Early Insight</h3>
        <p class="assembly-outcome-desc">Civic Briefs and Societal Readiness Index updates are shared with the Assembly before public release. You understand emerging concerns as they crystallize.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="assembly-outcome reveal reveal-d3">
        <h3 class="assembly-outcome-title">Selection Credibility</h3>
        <p class="assembly-outcome-desc">Being selected—not purchased—into the Founding Assembly signals something to the market, to regulators, and to your own organization about your commitment to AI readiness.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="assembly-outcome reveal reveal-d4">
        <h3 class="assembly-outcome-title">Collective Intelligence</h3>
        <p class="assembly-outcome-desc">Access to the accumulated wisdom of 25 institutions navigating AI readiness together. Shared frameworks, shared challenges, shared progress.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="assembly-outcome reveal reveal-d5">
        <h3 class="assembly-outcome-title">Permanent Association</h3>
        <p class="assembly-outcome-desc">The Founding Assembly closes at 25 institutions. Your organization's early commitment is recorded permanently in the infrastructure you helped build.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- ============================================
     THE PROCESS
     ============================================ -->
<section class="assembly-process">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="assembly-process-header">
      <span class="label label--accent reveal">The Process</span>
      <h2 class="assembly-process-title reveal">How Selection Works</h2>
      <p class="assembly-process-sub reveal">
        We do not accept applications. Founding Institutions are vetted and invited. However, you may express interest:
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="assembly-process-steps reveal">
      <div class="assembly-process-step">
        <span class="assembly-process-num">01</span>
        <div>
          <h3 class="assembly-process-step-title">Expression of Interest</h3>
          <p class="assembly-process-step-desc">Submit a brief form indicating your organization's alignment with our mission and criteria. This begins—but does not guarantee—the vetting process.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="assembly-process-step">
        <span class="assembly-process-num">02</span>
        <div>
          <h3 class="assembly-process-step-title">Vetting</h3>
          <p class="assembly-process-step-desc">We review your organization's public AI track record, leadership engagement, and values alignment. This is not a formality—we decline organizations that don't meet our criteria.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="assembly-process-step">
        <span class="assembly-process-num">03</span>
        <div>
          <h3 class="assembly-process-step-title">Invitation</h3>
          <p class="assembly-process-step-desc">If selected, you receive a formal invitation to join the Founding Assembly. The invitation includes the Charter and full details of commitments required.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="assembly-process-step">
        <span class="assembly-process-num">04</span>
        <div>
          <h3 class="assembly-process-step-title">Acceptance</h3>
          <p class="assembly-process-step-desc">Your CEO or equivalent signs the Founding Institution Charter. Your organization's name is added to the Assembly and the public record.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="assembly-process-step">
        <span class="assembly-process-num">05</span>
        <div>
          <h3 class="assembly-process-step-title">Onboarding</h3>
          <p class="assembly-process-step-desc">Welcome to the Founding Assembly. You're briefed on upcoming sessions, introduced to fellow Founding Institutions, and begin your active participation.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- ============================================
     ASSEMBLY STATUS
     ============================================ -->
<section class="assembly-status">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="assembly-status-inner reveal">
      <div class="assembly-status-content">
        <h2 class="assembly-status-title">The Assembly Will Close at 25 Institutions</h2>
        <p class="assembly-status-text">
          The Founding Assembly is currently being constituted. We are in dialogue with organizations across healthcare, finance, government, and technology. Once 25 Founding Institutions have been selected and have signed the Charter, the Assembly closes permanently to new members.
        </p>
        <p class="assembly-status-text">
          This is not artificial scarcity. 25 mirrors the structure of our TownSquare sessions—intimate enough for genuine dialogue, diverse enough for cross-sector insight. The institutions that build this infrastructure will be recorded as its founders.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- ============================================
     EXPRESSION OF INTEREST
     ============================================ -->
<section class="assembly-interest section--dark" id="interest">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="assembly-interest-inner">
      <div class="assembly-interest-header">
        <span class="label label--highlight reveal">Begin the Process</span>
        <h2 class="assembly-interest-title reveal">Expression of Interest</h2>
        <p class="assembly-interest-sub reveal">
          Submitting this form does not constitute an application. It signals your organization's interest and begins our vetting process. We respond to aligned organizations within 14 days.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="assembly-interest-grid">
        <div class="assembly-interest-context reveal">
          <h3 class="assembly-interest-context-title">What We Review</h3>
          <div class="assembly-interest-items">
            <div class="assembly-interest-item">
              <span class="assembly-interest-item-icon">
                <svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2">
                  <polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"/>
                </svg>
              </span>
              <span>Your organization's public AI initiatives and governance</span>
            </div>
            <div class="assembly-interest-item">
              <span class="assembly-interest-item-icon">
                <svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2">
                  <polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"/>
                </svg>
              </span>
              <span>Leadership statements and engagement on AI readiness</span>
            </div>
            <div class="assembly-interest-item">
              <span class="assembly-interest-item-icon">
                <svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2">
                  <polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"/>
                </svg>
              </span>
              <span>Track record of stakeholder-oriented decision making</span>
            </div>
            <div class="assembly-interest-item">
              <span class="assembly-interest-item-icon">
                <svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2">
                  <polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"/>
                </svg>
              </span>
              <span>Capacity and willingness to actively contribute</span>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="assembly-interest-contact">
            <p class="assembly-interest-contact-label">For direct inquiries</p>
            <a href="mailto:assembly@aitownsquare.org" class="assembly-interest-contact-email">assembly@aitownsquare.org</a>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="assembly-interest-form-wrap reveal reveal-d1">
          <form id="assemblyForm" action="https://formspree.io/f/{{ site.formspreeId }}" method="POST">
            <input type="hidden" name="_subject" value="Expression of Interest - Founding Assembly" />
            <input type="hidden" name="inquiry_type" value="founding_assembly" />

            <div class="form-group">
              <label class="form-label">Organization Name *</label>
              <input type="text" class="form-input" name="organization" required />
            </div>

            <div class="form-row">
              <div class="form-group">
                <label class="form-label">Contact Name *</label>
                <input type="text" class="form-input" name="contact_name" required />
              </div>
              <div class="form-group">
                <label class="form-label">Title / Role *</label>
                <input type="text" class="form-input" name="role" required />
              </div>
            </div>

            <div class="form-group">
              <label class="form-label">Email *</label>
              <input type="email" class="form-input" name="email" required />
            </div>

            <div class="form-group">
              <label class="form-label">Sector *</label>
              <select class="form-select" name="sector" required>
                <option value="">Select primary sector</option>
                <option value="healthcare">Healthcare</option>
                <option value="finance">Finance</option>
                <option value="government">Government</option>
                <option value="technology">Technology</option>
                <option value="multiple">Multiple Sectors</option>
              </select>
            </div>

            <div class="form-group">
              <label class="form-label">Why does your organization belong in the Founding Assembly? *</label>
              <textarea class="form-textarea" name="alignment" rows="4" placeholder="Describe your organization's demonstrated commitment to responsible AI and what you would contribute to the collective work" required></textarea>
            </div>

            <div class="form-group">
              <label class="form-label">Link to public evidence of AI commitment</label>
              <input type="url" class="form-input" name="evidence_link" placeholder="https://" />
              <span class="form-hint">Published research, governance framework, policy contribution, etc.</span>
            </div>

            <button type="submit" class="form-submit">
              Submit Expression of Interest <span class="btn-arrow">&rarr;</span>
            </button>

            <p class="form-disclaimer">
              This submission begins the vetting process. We will review your organization against our selection criteria and respond within 14 days if we wish to continue dialogue.
            </p>
          </form>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
